text.4508: I’m very excited about the future of #plantbased meat. With the global conv. meat market worth >$1T, there is plenty of room for more innovation in alt proteins to meet consumer needs while helping address climate change, resource scarcity, food security, and pandemic prevention.
text.4509: Zooming out, global retail dollar sales of #plantbased meat reached $6.1 billion in 2022, up 8% from 2021 with ton sales up 5%. In other words, in 2022, people around the globe spent more on plant-based meat than ever before. (Based on @Euromonitor data.) https://t.co/a9ohC9djKM
text.4510: Big picture: Today, #plantbased meat makes up 1.3% of total meat in U.S. retail, or 2.5% of packaged meat. In natural channel (where retail trends tend to start) like Sprouts and Natural Grocers and co-ops, plant-based meat makes up 15% of packaged meat dollar sales.
text.4511: #Plantbased meat dollar sales in U.S. retail have taken off in the last decade. In fact, 40% of dollar sales from the last 15 years came from just the last 3 years. https://t.co/ysCjNWzgn4
text.4512: Lots of headlines in the last year would have you believe that #plantbased meat is over/a fad. But the reality is that plant-based meat is a sizable category with clear pockets of growth. While it is facing real challenges, it also has a large runway for future development.
text.4513: I’ve been thinking deeply about where the #plantbased meat industry is today vs. where it was a decade ago, and what challenges it faces for sustained growth. 🧵
